00:23:41.625 --> 00:23:44.605
We, in the end, got a settlement of that dispute.

520
00:23:45.265 --> 00:23:46.805
We only got a settlement

521
00:23:46.955 --> 00:23:50.125
because that industrial action was disruptive

522
00:23:50.635 --> 00:23:53.405
because the government had to pass resolutions

523
00:23:53.405 --> 00:23:55.485
because those Defense Force

524
00:23:56.205 --> 00:23:58.685
civilian personnel took the very brave

525
00:23:58.705 --> 00:24:02.005
and difficult decision to continue taking industrial action

526
00:24:02.065 --> 00:24:04.525
to get a better outcome for them and their families.

527
00:24:04.825 --> 00:24:05.885
And I just wanna talk about

528
00:24:05.885 --> 00:24:07.485
who these civilian personnel are.

529
00:24:08.075 --> 00:24:10.365
They are absolutely critical people

530
00:24:10.905 --> 00:24:14.925
to the combat ready nature of the New Zealand Defense Force.

531
00:24:14.945 --> 00:24:17.565
The New Zealand Defense Force is only able to operate well

532
00:24:17.715 --> 00:24:21.045
because of the dedication of civilian personnel.

533
00:24:21.475 --> 00:24:25.085
They include people like diesel engineers, security guards,

534
00:24:25.345 --> 00:24:26.365
IT specialists,

535
00:24:26.985 --> 00:24:29.205
and the administrators who make sure

536
00:24:29.715 --> 00:24:33.325
that the military are able to serve properly, both here

537
00:24:33.345 --> 00:24:35.885
and overseas, who do all the work in the background.

538
00:24:36.075 --> 00:24:39.165
They're absolutely critical to the backbone

539
00:24:39.585 --> 00:24:42.365
of the New Zealand Defense Force, and they should be valued,

540
00:24:42.505 --> 00:24:44.925
and their ability to take industrial action should be

541
00:24:44.925 --> 00:24:48.325
celebrated because they needed to, to achieve things

542
00:24:48.345 --> 00:24:49.445
for them and their families.

543
00:24:49.445 --> 00:24:51.445
And the most recent industrial dispute is

544
00:24:51.485 --> 00:24:52.605
a clear example of that.

545
00:24:53.155 --> 00:24:55.845
They were offered nothing, including on the radio

546
00:24:56.665 --> 00:24:58.045
by the chief of the Defense Force.

547
00:24:58.555 --> 00:25:00.565
They took a series of industrial action,

548
00:25:00.625 --> 00:25:04.125
and in the end, we got a thousand dollars to every worker,

549
00:25:04.625 --> 00:25:05.965
and also a commitment

550
00:25:06.035 --> 00:25:09.365
that trades based roles would be properly valued

551
00:25:09.385 --> 00:25:11.565
and that the union and the employer would work on them.

552
00:25:12.195 --> 00:25:15.645
None of that was possible except for the fact

553
00:25:15.645 --> 00:25:18.245
that we were able to undertake a campaign

554
00:25:18.265 --> 00:25:19.365
of industrial action

555
00:25:19.365 --> 00:25:22.605
because civilian defense personnel had had enough.

556
00:25:23.195 --> 00:25:26.365
They were constantly told that they weren't valuable,

557
00:25:26.715 --> 00:25:29.965
that their value was, was to be determined by the employer,

558
00:25:30.065 --> 00:25:31.645
not to be agreed between them and the union.

559
00:25:32.225 --> 00:25:34.245
So I just want to break and, and even then,

560
00:25:34.415 --> 00:25:36.565
after all the industrial action

561
00:25:36.625 --> 00:25:40.125
and all the disruption that occurred, it was only able

562
00:25:40.125 --> 00:25:43.085
to take place because we went to facilitation

563
00:25:43.085 --> 00:25:45.485
with the Employment Relations Authority over a period

564
00:25:45.585 --> 00:25:47.605
of three days in a confidential setting

565
00:25:48.185 --> 00:25:49.725
and agreed an outcome.

566
00:25:49.865 --> 00:25:51.885
We also agreed to rebuild the relationship

567
00:25:51.955 --> 00:25:55.445
between the civilian personnel and the Defense Force.

568
00:25:56.385 --> 00:25:58.245
And I just wanna say as well,

569
00:25:58.675 --> 00:26:01.525
that these personnel had incredible support

570
00:26:02.075 --> 00:26:03.525
from their military colleagues.

571
00:26:04.915 --> 00:26:06.565
They said they do not want

572
00:26:06.565 --> 00:26:09.165
to be undermining them in their strike action.

573
00:26:09.275 --> 00:26:11.525
They said that privately to us, they,

574
00:26:11.715 --> 00:26:14.565
that the whole approach of using the military

575
00:26:14.585 --> 00:26:17.725
as replacement labor is incredibly divisive.

576
00:26:17.985 --> 00:26:20.845
And that is particularly problematic in a defense force.

577
00:26:21.525 --> 00:26:23.405
A defense force needs to act as one.

578
00:26:23.715 --> 00:26:25.245
It's part of the strength of it.

579
00:26:25.755 --> 00:26:28.765
This bill is damaging, it's divisive and it's dangerous,

580
00:26:28.765 --> 00:26:31.405
and we ask that you don't proceed with it.

581
00:26:32.395 --> 00:26:36.005
What we want to do is have a equal footing relationship.

582
00:26:36.065 --> 00:26:38.365
We want to be respected when we come

583
00:26:38.365 --> 00:26:39.405
and advocate on behalf

584
00:26:39.405 --> 00:26:41.205
of civilian personnel to the employer.

585
00:26:41.465 --> 00:26:44.365
We don't want to have to take disruptive industrial action.

586
00:26:44.905 --> 00:26:47.325
But that will keep happening if the Chief

587
00:26:47.325 --> 00:26:50.605
of the Defense Force keeps announcing zero payoffs.

588
00:26:50.605 --> 00:26:53.005
And look, I'm hopeful that won't happen in the future given

589
00:26:53.145 --> 00:26:55.205
the improved relationship we have

590
00:26:55.375 --> 00:26:56.885
after this industrial action.

591
00:26:57.425 --> 00:26:59.645
But I just wanna also say that this government's record

592
00:26:59.705 --> 00:27:01.365
and defense is very problematic.

593
00:27:01.855 --> 00:27:04.085
We've lost lots of civilian personnel.

594
00:27:04.525 --> 00:27:07.045
141 of them took voluntary redundancy.

595
00:27:07.285 --> 00:27:09.205
A whole bunch more have been restructured out,

596
00:27:09.275 --> 00:27:10.645
vacancies haven't been filled.

597
00:27:11.225 --> 00:27:14.245
The Defense Force civilian personnel are being starved

598
00:27:14.265 --> 00:27:17.765
of their ability to properly operate in the Defense Force

599
00:27:18.305 --> 00:27:20.325
and to be valued and respected.

600
00:27:21.465 --> 00:27:24.565
Um, we are worried that the practical implications

601
00:27:24.565 --> 00:27:27.245
of this bill will be very problematic as well.

602
00:27:27.535 --> 00:27:30.165
There isn't, uh, the appropriate training

603
00:27:30.265 --> 00:27:31.805
for military personnel to do many

604
00:27:31.805 --> 00:27:33.285
of the civilian personnel tasks.

605
00:27:33.865 --> 00:27:36.245
We are worried that there's less parliamentary scrutiny.

606
00:27:36.905 --> 00:27:38.045
But at the end of the day,

607
00:27:38.045 --> 00:27:39.725
what we are really worried about is

608
00:27:39.725 --> 00:27:41.445
that this undermines the ability

609
00:27:41.505 --> 00:27:44.645
of civilian defense personnel to be properly valued

610
00:27:44.745 --> 00:27:46.965
and to stand up for themselves and their families.

611
00:27:47.425 --> 00:27:50.445
And I spoke to them individually, many of them in advance

612
00:27:50.445 --> 00:27:51.565
of our facilitation.

613
00:27:52.105 --> 00:27:54.925
And what they told me is that their families

614
00:27:55.475 --> 00:27:58.365
were sacrificing their own wellbeing

615
00:27:58.435 --> 00:28:00.605
because they were committed to the defense force.

616
00:28:01.365 --> 00:28:03.365
I was astonished at the low pay

617
00:28:03.675 --> 00:28:05.845
that we were expecting civilian personnel

618
00:28:05.845 --> 00:28:07.485
to operate in our defense force on.

619
00:28:07.985 --> 00:28:11.085
So they need all the help they can get in bargaining better

620
00:28:11.155 --> 00:28:13.605
from the Defense Force, and this takes away from that.

